	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=1479&amp;mid=100364683674949">Helm changes colors!!</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=1479&amp;mid=100364683674949#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sun, Oct 21st 2:47 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=112115"><span id=" ">Ruok</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">2 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>This has to be one of the coolest items I have ever seen.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am an erudite, and when I wear the helm it is the same color as whatever gloves I am wearing.  I always thought the helm was green, because when I got it I was wearing RFV gloves.  However, I just got the thurgadin quest gloves; when I put on the new gloves, the helm turned tan!  I decided to try a few more gloves, and sure enough the helm changed colors every time I changed gloves.  This is quite convenient!  No matter what, the FFH will always match the color of your gloves.<br/><br/>BTW I waited for the druid in LFay to spawn for 5-6 hours a day for over a week with no luck.  She finally spawned when the server came back up after a patch.  I logged in and there she was, right where these boards say she is.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
