	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=71614"><span id=" ">Eitsekur</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">119 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.63]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Alas, this is not that cool.<br/><br/>I'm not sure what server you play on, or whether this affects other servers, but on 7th Hammer, erudite helm color is affected by your glove color.<br/><br/>Example 1: When I was level 4, I was given a Bronze Helm and a pair of Soft Wicker Gloves. Imagine my delight when my helm was green to match my gloves, very cool.<br/><br/>Example 2: In NRo, I was hunting, and a member of my group, a twinked erudite Shadow Knight, gave me a flayed skin cap. I put it on, and it appeared black (matching my Blackened Alloy Gaunlets).<br/><br/>Example 3: I bought a Skull Shaped Barbute while hunting Treants in South Karana. Still had Blackened Alloy Gauntlets, and surprise surprise, my shiny Barbute was *gasp* black.<br/><br/>Example 4: I wear a Sentient Helm, and a pair of Royal Frosted Velium Gauntlets. My helm appears dark dark green (almost black).<br/><br/>I've emailed GMs about it, and customer service, but no luck. Erudites will never be able to have clashing helmet / gauntlet colors...*sigh*<br/><br/>Eitsekur<br/>42 Shadow Knight (Erudite)<br/>Mythrilmoon Mystics, 7th Hammer</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
